    {
      "content": "The database will continue to work through the upgrade operation.",
      "pos": [
        4026,
        4091
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At the time of the actual transition to the new performance level temporary dropping of the connections to the database can happen for a very small duration (typically measured in seconds).",
      "pos": [
        4092,
        4281
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If an application has transient fault handling for connection terminations then it is sufficient to protect against dropped connections at the end of the upgrade.",
      "pos": [
        4282,
        4444
      ]
    },
